SIMPLE: storehouse
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Storehouse
<hw>Store"house`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
building for keeping goods of any kind, especially provisions; a
magazine; a repository; a warehouse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Joseph opened all the <qex>storehouses</qex>, and sold unto
Egyptians.</q> <rj><qau>Gen. xli. 56.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Scripture of God is a <qex>storehouse</qex> abounding with
estimable treasures of wisdom and knowledge.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A mass or quality laid up.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Storekeeper</ent>⟦br⟧
